//This shows you how to make another class and call it

public class sumClass {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
  int i = 4;
  int j = 5;
  int s = sum(i, j);  //defining int s as class sum
  System.out.println("The sum is " + s);  
  printSum(i, j);   //You don't need a system.out in this case, since it's already defined in the class
  } //end main
  
  public static int sum(int i, int j) {
    return i + j;   //because the return type is int, you need to use the return method
    }//end class declaration
  } //end sum
  
  public static void printSum(int i, int j) {
  private int a = 0;  //it's a private int so the value of this int doesn't get read in any other class, it's only for this class
  a = i + j;
    System.out.println("The sum is " + a);    //Because the return type is void, you have to have the system.out in the class
   }  //end printSum
} //end class


Console:

The sum is 9        //printed from line 8, using the sum class
The sum is 9        //printed from line 9, using the printSum class
